text: Okunino () is a village in Gmina Miastko, Bytów County, Pomeranian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It is about south-west of Bytów and south- west of Gdańsk (capital city of the Pomeranian Voivodeship). From 1975 to 1998 the village was in Słupsk Voivodeship. ==References== * *Map of the Gmina Miastko Category:Villages in Pomeranian Voivodeship
